  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the theft of $25,000, coupled with the fact that partial restitution has already been made and there is a documented motivation of personal debt, justifies a more lenient sentence than the statutory maximum. Taking into account deterrence and the necessity of punishment, a period of six months is appropriate for rehabilitation and accountability.",
  "verdict": 6
}
